entries.femaleVariant: Nearly there.
Ngh. End's in sight.
Fuckin' hell.
Stop there.
Song's dyin'.
Can't let you take her.
Reed, she's fuckin' dyin'.
You're not takin' her anywhere.
I see two near-corpses with a death wish. Your fault alone if she kicks it.
Spare me the quotes straight outta Bushido Ten.
Right, 'cause you and Myers had no hand in this shit.
Told you to stop!
Fuck off, for all time.
Stop where you are or die.
Slow, now…
That an order?
Fuck off.
You heard me.
Death – it's all that awaits her on the Moon. You wanna save 'er? Leave 'er to me.
Look at 'er, V! Be serious. You wanna send 'er to the Moon? Our neurosurgeons are her only chance.
I give you my word.
Final warnin'.
Gonna have to kill me.
She's yours to take… over my dead body.
Damn, am I ever sorry, V.
[Holster weapon] Take her, all yours.
She plain turned us down.
Tried to help her, both of us. Get 'er out of this – we wanted it, badly.
Left us no choice. It's how the dice fall sometimes.
That an order?
[Lay Songbird down] Easy, now.
[Lay Songbird down] Don't shoot..
[Lay Songbird down] If that's the way you put it…
One more step and you're dead!
Don't provoke me.
So, whaddaya wanna do?
Need to know if you're with me.
'Ey, V!
We're not done yet.
V!
You hear what I said?
What's with you, girl?
Playin' for time?
The situation's changed. Just leave Songbird to me, I can still help 'er.
[Draw weapon] Not afraid of you.
Won't be able to forgive yourself.
Song –  what'll happen to her?
Heard you talkin' to Myers.
Touch her and you're dead.
Back on the roof, Myers ordered her killed, you didn't protest.
You heard us.
Reach for her, and I'll kill you.
Final warnin'…
Assumin' you guys do save her life, what then? What'll happen to 'er?
entries.maleVariant: Assumin' you guys do save her life, what then, what'll happen to 'er?

entries.femaleVariant: So Mi wants above all to survive. I'm her last and only hope now.
[Draw weapon] Sorry, man.
C'mon, man, do this 'n' you'll kill 'er. Kill her, me… your own damn self, too. Fuckin' remorse alone'll get ya.
Don't shoot! So be it, Song's yours. Just one condition.
You got three seconds.
One.
Dammit to hell, Reed!
Reed…
Two.
[Draw weapon] Sorry, man.
Reed...
[Holster weapon] Take her. Don't want nothin' in return.
[Draw weapon] Sorry, man.
Reed, dammit!
[Holster weapon] All yours, but you'll help me live on.
Song regretted selling you out.
Want Song? Over my dead body.
[Draw weapon] Not givin' 'er up to you.
Grow the hell up. Came to terms with my personal failure way back.
You'll take her over my dead body. If she dies, she'll die a free woman.
She wanted out and away. From you, Myers, the FIA… Said so.
Your past… you can't just escape it. I know what I'm talkin' about.
How would you? Never tried it yourself.
I'm just not naive, V.
[Draw weapon] No way either you or me'll come around…
Sure as hell responsible for Songbird.
FIA's done with you.
Song mentioned her Militech datafort raid. How you swooped in, prevented her brain from fryin'.
But then you fuckin' billed her for it, in small print. No way, no day she could pay it off.
I gave her a choice. The FIA or a NetWatch interrogation chamber.
Some fuckin' choice. More like blackmail. Locked her in a cage for a shit-stained decade.
Myers doe'n't trust you no more.
entries.maleVariant: Myers don't trust you no more.

entries.femaleVariant: Thinkin' to get back in her good graces? By deliverin' So Mi on a platter?
This is not about me.
That biz seven years ago? Song followed Myers' order, then never forgave herself for it.
Solomon Reed – loyal soldier of the NUSA.
Betrayed me too, Song did.
Understand a lot more than you do. You ain't doin' this for the NUS… or for Myers.
Pff. You're right. Song's curb stomped everyone to get what she wants. Condemned me to death.
entries.maleVariant: Ah. You're right. Song's curb stomped everyone to get what she wants. Condemned me to death.

entries.femaleVariant: Pawns – that's how Myers treats you.
Doubt you know what freedom is.
No honor, Reed? None at all?
Myers… her army days're long forgotten. Militech's shaped her thinking. Significant, I'd say. Makes peeps spare parts to her.
entries.maleVariant: Myers… her army days're long forgotten. Militech's shaped her thinking. Significant, I say, it… makes peeps spare parts to her.

entries.femaleVariant: While you remain a soldier. Loyalty – know its meaning and value.
entries.maleVariant: While you remain a soldier. Loyalty – know its meanin' and value.

entries.femaleVariant: Matter's simple, I think – you don't sell your friends down the river.
entries.maleVariant: Matter's simple, I think. You don't sell your friends down the river.

entries.femaleVariant: Song and I, we're federal agents. That simplifies some things, makes others more complicated. In any case, it ain't street rules, no.
Never really been free, have you. Can't understand slippin' outta the collar, off the leash, how much that could mean to So Mi.
entries.maleVariant: Never really been free, have ya. Can't understand slippin' outta the collar, off the leash, how much that could mean to So Mi.

entries.femaleVariant: Freedom's not youthful upheaval. And it certainly ain't a way to run from trouble.
Really rather not kill you.
Ain't no savin' me nohow…
Really don't wanna shoot you.
Same. So just turn around and walk away.
[Holster weapon] She's yours. Take her.
Can't give you So Mi. Won't.
Can't hand 'er over. Won't.
[Draw weapon] Enough o' this.
[Draw weapon] This ends now.
[Draw weapon] Nope, not takin' her anywhere.
Soldiers don't question orders. They follow them.
She's fleein' 'cause she grew up, realized she was bein' used.
It takes sacrifice to serve an ideal, V.
You'd think comrades in arms'd be loyal. On the streets or in the FIA…
When you have an ideal, you stick by it.
Don't come any closer.
Don't come any closer.
Promi--
Europe – said you know peeps there…
Mmmm…
Move an inch and I'll kill you, V, I will.
Want just one thing. To survive, live on.
You're empty-handed, got nothin' to offer – you, the FIA, fuckin' NUS with Myers at its helm. Empty-handed.
Every last word.
Best clinic, you said. Promised me a place there.
Just one dose, one instance of the cure exists. Song decided to keep it, but...
Deal.
Left me with nothin'…
I see. So Songbird for me, that one dose for you.
Need the cure and the rippers who know how to use it. Mentioned contacts in Europe, personal ones.
Deal. Take her. But don't fuckin' let me die.
entries.maleVariant: Deal. Take 'er. But don't fuckin' let me die.

entries.femaleVariant: Just... take 'er. Got no right to trade her life for anything. Don't wanna.
entries.maleVariant: Just take 'er. I got no right to trade her life for anything. Don't wanna.

entries.femaleVariant: Your choice.
Had enough. You can have 'er.
Look, look, puttin' 'er down.
Spit it out.
Gonna be the same for you. Remorse to the end of your days.
Lemme guess – she promised, then she didn't deliver.
[Holster weapon] Deal.
[Holster weapon] She's yours, but I want nothing in return.
Neural matrix – how'll you get it back?
How'm I to know your people'll recover the neural matrix? Any guarantee?
I can't pretend to know this shit inside out. Remember, though, Cynosure's our tech.
Song – what'll happen to her?
Say I survive. What happens to Song, dare I ask?
We'll do our damndest to stop the Blackwall degeneration, look for other ways.
Myers wants Song dead, condemned her already.
You really mixed that up. You're not slavin' just 'cause you have a duty. And… So Mi swore an oath.
You'll lock 'er in a cage again. Last thing she'd ever want.
entries.maleVariant: You'll lock her in a cage again. Last thing she'd ever want.

entries.femaleVariant: Doin' this for you alone. Without it? You're nothin', no one.
I'm sorry, man.
Cure – just one dose of it exists.
You're fakin'. You're not interested in this.
Care about me that much? Outta nowhere?
Myers owes you her life. And she pays her debts.
How you gonna help me, exactly?
Neural matrix – how'll you get it back?
Song – what'll happen to her?
In Europe, at Langley, too. The NUSA's specialists are top of the game.
But with this, we're even.
Myers couldn't let 'er escape. If we get her, alive, have 'er in our hands, the NUSA'll be safe, Songbird'll live.
Outta my way, Reed.
They'll pull the data for you, then operate. Do we have a deal?
I'm takin' Songbird to Washington. She'll answer for treason, she has to.
But this ain't about Song anymore, V. No, this is about her not sparkin' another war.
Been hidin' behind the NUS flag all your life. Come a day they'll drape it over your casket.
You'll never understand.
But carin' about So Mi, I strove to help her. Well, she shat all over everything I could say in her defense. 'S gonna drag you down, too.
Leave her to me. And save yourself.
Nuh-uh, V. Try me first.
Got nothin' I want, nothin' you can give me…
Wanna live on.
Wanna survive, live on.
[Holster weapon] Take her. Don't want nothin' in return.
Don't shoot! So be it, Song's yours.
Simple as that? No hagglin'?
Simple as that. Just take her.
Dose and what's needed, including pro peeps handy with a scalpel.
Mentioned contacts in Europe, one holo away?
entries.maleVariant: Mentioned contacts in Europe, one holo away.

entries.femaleVariant: Song was willin' to fly to Luna for the surgery. Quite a ways, that.
Me? Just need the best damn clinic on Terra.
Pioneering clinic workin' at the cuttin' edge, NUSA's finest specialists at your bedside.
Just as you swore. Remember that?
And then decided to cast it aside. Betrayin' herself, betrayin' us. There's a price on that, she's gotta pay it.
Gave me no choice.
Not givin' 'er up, Sol. No.
Not afraid of you, Sol, no.
Ng-ghe-he…
It's the right choice.
N-no… I won't let you…
T-too… damn late…
Why? What f-for…?
Let's get this shit done…
[Lay Songbird down] Didn't want our help…
[Lay Songbird down] You were right – Song's a traitor.
Warned me about 'er, dammit.
I'm waitin'.
Betrayed Myers, you... then came my turn.
She was my friend once. Who she is today – I dunno.
Take 'er, all yours…
Hold up there.
Turned out to be a straight con. One not worth dyin' for…
Used me, she did.
Songbird fail to deliver what she promised?
Come the end, you made the right choice.
An' I won't be the one to judge 'er.
Straight con, she is. Not about to die for her.
entries.maleVariant: Straight con, she is. Not about to die for 'er.

entries.femaleVariant: Took us all for a ride. Don't feel I owe her a damn thing…
entries.maleVariant: Took us all for a ride. Don't feel I owe 'er a damn thing…

entries.femaleVariant: Just take 'er, don't want a thing from you.
I ain't naive. There's a price to pay, gotta be, I know that.
[Draw weapon] So Mi's not yours to take.
Just one dose, one instance of the cure exists. Song decided to keep it, but...
Left me with nothin'…
I hear ya. That one dose, that's your price.
Need the cure and the rippers who know how to use it. Mentioned contacts in Europe, personal ones.
In Europe, at Langley, too. The NUSA's specialists are top of the game.
I can do that. You get your cure, I take Songbird with me. Then we go our separate ways. Do we have a deal?
That's right. Offered me a cure, so make good on it.
How you gonna help me, exactly?
Deal.
She's yours, but I want nothing in return.
Neural matrix – how'll you get it back?
Song – what'll happen to her?
